Package: dtasamplesize
Type: Package
Title: Simulation-Based Sample Size Estimation for Diagnostic Accuracy Studies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jes\u00fas D.", "Rojas", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "jrojasrivero@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0912-490X")),
    person("Rafael", "Pichardo-Rodriguez", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provides simulation-based (Monte Carlo) methods for sample size
    estimation in diagnostic test accuracy (DTA) studies. Implements Bayesian
    assurance (Wilson et al. 2022 <doi:10.1002/sim.9393>), joint optimization
    of sensitivity, specificity, and AUC, adjustment for imperfect reference
    standards (Staquet et al. 1981 <doi:10.1016/0021-9681(81)90059-X>),
    adaptive prevalence re-estimation (Stark & Zapf 2020
    <doi:10.1177/0962280220913588>), sample size for time-dependent ROC
    curves, and sample size for net benefit (decision curve analysis).
    Addresses limitations of classical formulas (Buderer 1996
    <doi:10.1111/j.1553-2712.1996.tb03538.x>) demonstrated via Monte Carlo
    validation. Includes a unified framework that integrates all approaches.
